name: Sreeram Academy
aboutUs: The CPT or Common Proficiency Test is the first level of Chartered Accountancy examinations. A person can register for CPT after completing Class 10 and take the exam after completing High School (class12). It is an objective type examination and consists of 200 multiple choice questions. CPT covers four basic subjects divided into two sections viz. 1.Fundamentals of Accounting (60 Marks)+ Mercantile Laws(40 Marks) and 2.Economics(50 Marks)+ Quantitative Aptitude(50 Marks). Every incorrect answer on the CPT exam carries a 0.25 negative mark. A candidate is required to secure a minimum of 30 per cent marks in each Section and a minimum of 50 per cent marks in aggregate in all the four Sections to pass the Common Proficiency Test. CPT exams are held in June and December in paper pencil mode. On-line CPT exams are also conducted periodically. But with effect from 3rd Aug 2012 CPT is exempted for the Graduates, Post Graduates and the students having equivalent degrees. Commerce graduates with 55% and other graduates with 60% can take direct admission for IPCC.

name: Genius
aboutUs: During the course, the participants are blindfolded and train their sensory perceptions. The visual dominant people are able to see the colors and details in a flash card while blindfolded. The auditory dominant people are able to hear the colors and details in a flash card while blindfolded. The Touch dominant people are able to feel the colors and details in a flash card by touching. The Smell dominant people are able to smell the colors and details in a flash card by smelling. Those who are Taste dominant people are able to taste the colors and details in a flash card by putting the flash card near to the tongue. When the brainpower increases, the sensory perception improves. When the senses improve, the ability to comprehend is heightened. The five ?radars? are able to capture information from outside easily and download into the brain, hence improves learning capabilities.

Mahesh T

 attended 
Begin your Wing Chun Journey here !!!!!
 posted on 26 May, 2016

					"I was searching for the school for more than two hours going in circles around the area that was shown in map without a clue. No contacts. There is a body building gym at the same spot but no wing chun school. The place where it was, is not anymore. I respect the art of wing chun so much and I see it not only as a martial art, but a way of life. I believe it could inspire me. I felt like I was kind of lost. If anyone's out there who knows the way to reach this art in Chennai, please post here. It could help people like me.
									"', u'K












Kaleem

 attended 

 in Jul,2015
					
 posted on 15 Mar, 2016

					"Having trained in martial arts since my teen years I really enjoyed the kicking elements of the arts. After practicing kickboxing for 3 years I felt I needed an art that was tailored for self defence.In 2009 I was introduced to Wing Chun. I knew Bruce Lee had studied this art and I knew this had fast hands.I attended an introductory course with my friend Imran at sifu Shawn Rawcliffe’s school. I was impressed with the art for being unique, fast and a counter attacking style. Being a close quarter range martial arts system I had decided to pursue a journey in Wing Chun.
Myself and Imran had practiced the basics together over the years.It wasn’t until 2014 that I had to relocate for work in Warrington. There I met and trained under Sifu Jay Hussein (Ching Mo Wing Chun school) for a few months gaining a good insight to wing chun.The systems simple and direct approach have left me fascinated. I really enjoy training the sensitivity drills and applications of trapping and locking. After moving back home to Leicester the most interesting part of my journey commenced. I was fortunate to get in contact with Sifu Abid and join his school. Training under him I have found that he teaches wing chun with a very practical approach to modern day fighting / self defence and he explains why certain techniques work in a certain manner.He is by far one of the most humble and most patient instructors I have come across. Sifu’s teaching has always been demonstrated effectively.His multiple assailants drill has been a brilliant blood pumping exercise that simulates a real life scenario.
It has been a great privilege to learn from Sifu as he is very skilled and confident in what he teaches. Under his guidance I have seen an improvement in my technique and ability.Helping students in the class has been a rewarding experience especially when students progress in their ability and understanding of applications.
My desire is to gain an in depth understanding to the principals and theories of wing chun and be able to share that knowledge with other students.I look forward to learning and helping new students in the future.Most importantly I would like to thank sifu for teaching us with so much dedication."', u'K












Kashif Amin

 attended 

 in Jun,2012
					
 posted on 15 Mar, 2016

					"“I have been training with Sifu Abid from the Midlands Wing Chun Association for the past few years, and cannot recommend him highly enough. Sifu Abid’s classes are always disciplined, energetic and inspirational. Through the course of my training, I have grown in confidence in my own abilities and application of Wing Chun. His training has helped me to improve coordination, stamina, body strength, dexterity and endurance. Sifu Abid is very experienced and has the innate ability to tailor his lessons to people of all ages and backgrounds. This has been especially evident with my children (son aged 6yrs and daughter aged 8yrs), who regularly attend the children’s sessions. They engage in the lessons with great energy and enthusiasm, supported by Sifu Abid’s guidance and encouragement. Training with Sifu Abid has enabled us to appreciate the amazing depth and diversity of the Wing Chun Kung Fu martial art.”
"', u'I












Imran Mukerdam

 attended 

 in Sep,2013
					
 posted on 15 Mar, 2016

					"Having practiced Karate at a young age, I was familiar with punching and kicking with flexibility, discipline and order.Later on in 2009 me and my friend Arif were introduced to Wing Chun.
After attending an introductory course with Sifu Shaun Rawcliffe, we were impressed by its uniqueness and explosiveness. We practiced the basics together that we had learnt until 2014. During this time (2009 – 2014) I would research with interest into the art of Wing Chun. The more I researched the more interested I became.
Due to work commitments I never had the chance to dedicate my time to Wing Chun. I would read books and watch videos and try and train through these methods instead. My friend Arif had the opportunity to learn some Wing Chun in Warrington. We would meet on weekends and practice and improve what we knew.
Now that we are fortunate and have met Sifu Abid, we have had the opportunity to learn so much from Sifu’s teaching experience. Learning from someone very patient and skilled like Sifu has really progressed our Wing Chun in a couple months.
It is wonderful to see him demonstrate his knowledge every lesson and see how Wing Chun uses science and bio-mechanics instead of physical brute strength. Training under a well accomplished Sifu who is humble has really given me a far better understanding and grasp of the concept of Wing Chun.
It is Sifu Abid’s teaching ability and experience that makes him an ideal teacher.
I would definitely recommend Sifu Abid to anyone who wants to learn Wing Chun."']

name: Knowbigdata
aboutUs: KnowBigData provides quality online trainings by instructors who are industry experts. The focus is on learning to solve real world problems and a very hands on learning experience.  We pride ourselves in the quality of our instructors and our customer centric approach. Our trainers are experts in Big Data and in explaining difficult concepts in the most simplified ways. They are generally Architects or technology leaders in Big Data product firms. Passionate about sharing knowledge, some of them are also regular contributors to Big Data products.We provide a cluster or cloud which is accessible 24x7 from everywhere. The big data technologies are all about distributed computing and the knowledge is incomplete if the real cluster hands on experimentations are not done. The cluster is available to you till you finish your project.Based on your performance in the course, we provide the certificate in various forms: PDF sent to your email, a permanent web page with your pic that may come in google search results, a linked recommendation and endorsement.Using graphics, animation, analogies, and storytelling, we explain very complex topics in ways easy to understand and remember.While staying focused on current classes and feedbacks from our students, we also aim to stay connected with our past students. You can have lifelong access to the learning management system and to our instructors.

reviews:
[u'S












Subramonia

 attended 

 in Nov,2014
					
 posted on 16 Dec, 2014

					"?For a good couple of years, I was knocking on the doors of various audio institutes, to join an affordable course in Audio Engineering. Pouring over plenty of advertisements, websites and student testimonials, I made an inquiry with many an established institution.

Amidst all the running from pillar to post, I stumbled upon Dinesh Sir's contact. The one phone-call I made to him is one of the best decisions I have taken in my hitherto journey in music. Though I have been listening to thousands of songs across the last couple of decades, the Audio Engineering course in DYNAMICS School gave me an entirely different perspective to music, both from listening and mixing perspectives.

Moreover, I had an added restriction that I work in the corporate, and weekends are hence the only time slots I get to further my interest in music. I was highly fortunate that Sir readily agreed to starting off a weekend batch to accommodate the interests of people like me. Though classes were designated for three hours each on Saturday and Sunday, I don't remember a single instance where the class was wound up prior to at least four hours! Also, the course started off right from "What is sound?", which was the introductory topic in our Physics textbooks of the 9th Standard at school, practical assignments flowed in next. Audio mixing assignments for film trailers and songs made me learn either art to perfection. As I pen down my experience seated in the very class I have been learning for the last several months, I pause to reflect that the atmosphere has never felt like school, but more like home away from home. For, the sessions here are never academic. They are conversational, and there is a flow to every lesson being taught. Visits to nearby audio studios, getting to talk with experts who are involved in professional mixing, getting to know Sir's own experiences from his working in the industry, for over a decade,make this school a treasure trove of knowledge. Conveying a 'note of thanks' is the least I could do, for all the above.?
				"', u'T

The best work I do, the songs I mix or the projects I co-ordinate, the best work which come out with credits will always go to Mr. Dinesh. The days that I have been in this school has been the most rewarding and best learning days of my career. No one other than Mr. Dinesh can teach this gifted subject so professionally and the same time as easily that it reaches the amateur mind. I would always look back to this school as my growth ladder where ever I go.

					"When I first decided to become a musician, I never knew what to do and how to do. I came to Chennai with very little hope of learning something, however I joined Dynamics School of Audio Engineering and met one of my greatest inspirations, Mr. Dinesh Ramalingam Sir, who runs the show and is one of the best Audio Engineers by far. World class knowledge and a very dynamic thought process environment has now led me to be someone I always wanted to be. I run a full fledged audio recording studio in New Delhi, India, called "Arcube Records", and have worked for many big brands because of my audio production quality. If it was not for Sir, I would have never known this side of the field. I am forever grateful to Sir for all the brilliant lectures and amazing concepts. Things that people generally do not share because they have spent years to achieve it, Dinesh Sir would give it right away, as he always believed in us just the same as we did. To know about someone at once and recognise what he or she can do, needs a lot of knowledge, however it came naturally to Dinesh Sir! In Short : "Think of audio, Think of Dynamics" - Truly the best.
